THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 211 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. The sheriff, chief of police or town marshal responsible for
4 the operation of a county, city or town jail or detention facility
5 shall develop and implement a policy concerning the supervision,
6 custody, care, security, housing and medical and mental health
7 treatment of prisoners who are transgender, gender non-
8 conforming, gender non-binary and intersex. The policy must:
9 (a) Use respectful language and currently accepted
10 terminology that accounts for and protects the rights of prisoners
11 who are transgender, gender non-conforming, gender non-binary
12 and intersex;
13 (b) Prohibit the discrimination of prisoners who are
14 transgender, gender non-conforming, gender non-binary and
15 intersex;
16 (c) Include, or incorporate by reference, a provision which
17 designates the factors to be considered when assigning housing,
18 which must, without limitation, take into account the preference of
19 prisoners;
20 (d) Include, or incorporate by reference, a protocol for
21 searches, which:
22 (1) Includes considering the preference of a prisoner when
23 determining the gender of the officer assigned to conduct a
24 search; and
25 (2) Prohibits an unclothed search for the purpose of
26 observing the genitalia of a prisoner after initial intake into the
27 jail or detention facility, unless reasonable grounds exist;
28 (e) Require medical personnel to follow the applicable
29 standard of care when treating a prisoner who is transgender,
30 gender non-conforming, gender non-binary or intersex;
31 (f) Require, to the extent practicable, that a prisoner who is
32 transgender, gender non-conforming, gender non-binary or
33 intersex have access to preferred clothing, undergarments and
34 hygiene items, regardless of housing assignment;
35 (g) Include, or incorporate by reference, provisions that apply
36 to adult prisoners and juvenile prisoners; and
37 (h) Include, or incorporate by reference, a timely and fair
38 grievance or appeal process for any violation of the policy.
39 2. The sheriff, chief of police or town marshal responsible for
40 the operation of a county, city or town jail or detention facility
41 may develop and implement training for members of the staff of
42 the jail or detention facility in cultural competency for interacting
