1 with prisoners who are transgender, gender non-conforming,
2 gender non-binary and intersex.
3 3. Nothing in this section shall be construed to require a
4 county, city or town jail or detention facility to construct
5 additional buildings or facilities or to implement any additional
6 training for staff to comply with a policy developed pursuant to
7 this section.
8 4. As used in this section:
9 (a) “Gender non-binary” means a person whose gender
10 identity does not conform to the traditional gender binary of male
11 and female.
12 (b) “Gender non-conforming” means a person whose gender
13 characteristics or behaviors do not conform to those
14 characteristics or behaviors traditionally associated with the
15 biological sex of the person.
16 (c) “Intersex” means a condition in which a person is born
17 with external genitals, internal reproductive organs, chromosome
18 patterns or an endocrine system that does not conform to the
19 traditional gender binary of male or female.
20 (d) “Transgender” means a person whose gender identity or
21 expression differs from the sex assigned to the person at birth.
22 Sec. 2. (Deleted by amendment.)
